data.Name: Natural gas
data.Description: A Gas Product Type is a substance that exists in a non-solid or non-liquid state under normal temperatures and pressures. It possesses perfect molecular mobility and the property of indefinite expansion and is lighter than oil or water.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Methane
data.Description: Methane (CH4) is the lightest of the hydrocarbon gases.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Ethane
data.Description: Ethane (C2H6) is a hydrocarbon gas.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Ethane plus
data.Description: Ethane Plus is a mixture of ethane and higher molecular weight hydrocarbon gases, also known as C2+.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Propane
data.Description: Propane (C3H8) is a hydrocarbon gas.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Butane
data.Description: Butane (C4H10) is a hydrocarbon gas, occurring as normal butane (nC4) and isobutane (iC4).
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Pentane
data.Description: Pentane (C5H12) is a hydrocarbon gas.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Pentanes plus
data.Description: Pentanes Plus is a mixture of pentanes and higher molecular weight hydrocarbon gases, also known as C5+.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Condensate
data.Description: Condensate is a natural gas mixture that exists in a liquid state with a low vapor pressure compared with liquid petroleum gas (LPG). Condensate is mainly composed of propane, butane, pentane and heavier hydrocarbon fractions.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Liquid petroleum gas
data.Description: Liquid Petroleum gas (LPG) is a natural gas mixture composed of mainly ethane, propane, and butanes, with small amounts of pentanes plus (C5+) in any combination. The fluid is usually gaseous under atmospheric conditions but becomes a liquid under pressure.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Acid gas
data.Description: Acid Gas is a poisonous and corrosive gas mixture consisting of hydrogen sulfide and carbon dioxide in varying concentrations.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Non-hydrocarbon gas
data.Description: The Non-hydrocarbon Gas Product Type is gas that does not contain hydrocarbons. It is generally not flammable.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Air
data.Description: Air is a mixture of colourless, tasteless, invisible gases that surrounds the earth and are composed of mainly nitrogen and oxygen molecules.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Carbon dioxide
data.Description: Carbon Dioxide (C02) is a pure gaseous or liquid compound chemically composed of 1 carbon atom and 2 oxygen atoms.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Helium
data.Description: Helium (He) is a colorless, odorless, tasteless, non-toxic, inert monatomic gas produced as a by-product in certain oil and gas reservoirs.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Hydrogen
data.Description: Hydrogen is the lightest and most abundant chemical element.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Hydrogen sulfide
data.Description: Hydrogen Sulfide (H2S) is a colorless, transparent gas with a characteristic rotten-egg odor at low concentrations and not detectable by odor at higher concentrations. H2S is a toxic at very low concentration.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Nitrogen
data.Description: Nitrogen, used in various well treatments, is a colorless, odorless, tasteless and mostly inert diatomic gas at standard conditions.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Oxygen
data.Description: Oxygen (O2) is a colorless, odorless, tasteless diatomic gas.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Oil
data.Description: An Oil Product Type is a mixture of hydrocarbon substances that occurs as a viscous liquid. It is extracted by wells or mining and processed into fuels, lubricants, chemicals, etc.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Fine light oil
data.Description: Fine Light oil is crude oil with an API gravity > 45.0.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Premium light oil
data.Description: Premium Light oil is crude oil with an API gravity > 39.9 and < 45.1.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Light oil
data.Description: Light oil is crude oil with an API gravity > 31.1 and < 40.0.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Medium oil
data.Description: Medium oil is crude oil with an API gravity > 22.2 and < 31.2.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Heavy oil
data.Description: Heavy oil is crude oil with an API gravity > 9.9 and < 22.3.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Bitumen
data.Description: Bitumen oil is crude oil with an API gravity < 10.0.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Naphtha
data.Description: Naphtha is a colourless and highly volatile, flammable liquid hydrocarbon intermediate product between gasoline and benzene formed from the distillation of crude oil.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Mineral
data.Description: Mineral Product Types are nonhydrocarbon inorganic solids dissolved or carried in a fluid obtained from well operations.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Lithium
data.Description: Lithium is a chemical element. It may be extracted from oil and water.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Magnesium
data.Description: Magnesium is a chemical element. It may be extracted from oil and water.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Potash
data.Description: Potash is a general name of potassium-bearing salts. Potash may be extracted by using hot water to dissolve the potash and bring it to the surface through wells.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Mineral salts
data.Description: Mineral Salts include a broad range of iconic compounds that are made up of two groups of oppositely charged ions. Salts may be soluble in oil well fluids and are extracted during processing.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Sulfur
data.Description: Sulfur is a non-metallic element that can be extracted from Hydrogen Sulfide gas (H2S).
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Uranium
data.Description: Uranium is the chemical element of atomic number 92 , a gray, dense radioactive metal.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Water
data.Description: The Water Product Type is a chemical substance of hydrogen and oxygen (H2O). In common usage, water is the liquid phase. Water is denser than oil or gas.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Alkaline water
data.Description: Alkaline Water is a water-based fluid which has more hydroxyl ions (OH-) than hydrogen ions (H+) and pH greater than 7.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Brackish water
data.Description: Brackish Water has a salinity generally between 0.5 and 30.0 parts per thousand (ppt). The specific range of salinity may vary by agency.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Brine
data.Description: Brine Water has a salinity greater than (>) 50.0 parts per thousand (ppt).
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Salt water
data.Description: Salt Water has a salinity between 30.1 and 50.0 parts per thousand (ppt).
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Combination water
data.Description: Combination Water is water of differing salinity measurements.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Fresh water
data.Description: Fresh Water has a salinity less than (<) 0.5 parts per thousand (ppt).
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Geothermal fluid
data.Description: Geothermal Product Types are naturally heated fluids. They may be steam or hot water, and may contain salts, minerals, or other dissolved substances.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).

data.Name: Steam
data.Description: The Steam Product Type is water in the gas phase.
data.Source: Workbook curated by PPDM; commit SHA - No SHA (Workbook not committed).
